commentary_data: Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, ,  Prabhsimran certainly packs a punch! Full ball swinging in towards the pads, Prabhsimran whips it over square leg. The timing and the connection is great and the ball sails over the fence
Southee to Prabhsimran, , Southee gets his line awry and pays the price first ball. Swinging down leg, Prabhsimran clips it nonchalantly and Umesh Yadav at fine leg has no chance to cut it off

Southee to Prabhsimran, , Prabhsimran had a very good Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy recently and he is oozing confidence! He uses his feet and hammers the length ball past mid-off. Went through the field like a flash and he gets the desired result

Southee to Prabhsimran, , cracking shot! He doesn't care about reputations, does he? He uses his feet and converts this length ball into his arc. Tonks it over cow corner with a beautiful swing of the bat for a 86m six

Southee to Prabhsimran,  Caught by Gurbaz!!  Prabhsimran will be disappointed with himself but he has provided a flying start to his side. Good length ball swinging in on leg, he moves inside the line and tries to work it across, perhaps towards fine leg but he only manages a nick behind. Gurbaz moves to his left and takes a regulation catch.
Southee to Dhawan, ,  Back of a length ball and width on offer, Dhawan cashes in and plays a cracking cut shot. It's in the gap through covers and there is no stopping that

Southee to Dhawan, , back to back boundaries! Well played but Southee is feeding Dhawan to his strengths. This one is on a back of a length and there is even more room on offer, Dhawan doesn't miss out as he cuts it in between cover point and point to find the fence

Narine to Rajapaksa, , right on cue from Rajapaksa! He is a fearless batter. He premeditates and uses his feet and makes some room. Converts it into a half-volley and lifts it over long-off for maximum
Narine to Rajapaksa, , Rajapaksa once again uses his feet, goes inside out over extra cover to find the fence once again. Played that really nicely
Narine to Rajapaksa, , this is brilliant batting! Rajapaksa is once again nimble on his feet as he lifts it down the ground for a maximum. Straight as an arrow. 50 up for Punjab and 14 off the over
Chakaravarthy to Dhawan, , Dhawan backs away and opens up the off-side for himself, It's on a length and he cuts it with the spin over covers for a rocketing boundary,

Thakur to Rajapaksa, , Rajapaksa is once again nimble on his feet. He smashes the back of a length ball past the bowler. Umesh from long-on moves swiftly to his right, and dives full length to his right but can't keep the ball in play. A brilliant effort nonetheless
Thakur to Rajapaksa, ,  Length ball on leg, Rajapaksa in flamingo style plays a pick up flick shot. Makes good connection and clears the fine leg fence with ease. He is off to a flier
Narine to Rajapaksa, ,  On a length on leg, Rajapaksa connects with his sweep this time. Chakravarty dives to his right but makes a mess of it as the ball goes through him and to the boundary

Thakur to Rajapaksa, , deft from Rajapaksa! He has the power game as well as the touch game in his armoury. On a length outside off, Rajapaksa gets low in his stance and dabs it past the right of short fine to find the fence. Thakur changed to round the wicket but it didn't work for him

Thakur to Dhawan, , , poor from Thakur and he has been taken to the cleaners! High full toss outside off, Dhawan carves it away over backward point and picks up a one-bounce boundary. Thakur overstepped and Free Hit coming up..

Chakaravarthy to Dhawan, , expert batting from Dhawan! On a shorter length on off, Dhawan waits for it and pulls it nicely. Delayed his shot to find the gap and bisected deep mid-wicket and deep square leg to perfection
Chakaravarthy to Dhawan, 1 run, spinning away on a length from Dhawan. He looks to cut it away but ends up chopping it away towards backward point.

Umesh Yadav to Dhawan, , full and wide, Dhawan advances, reaches out and slices it away through backward point! That's beautifully timed! He had to really stretch to get to the ball, but still connected so well!
Umesh Yadav to Rajapaksa, 2 runs, full outside off, Rajapaksa goes much harder at it this time, and  It falls safely though after clearing extra cover. He gets back for two and

Umesh Yadav to Rajapaksa,  Caught by Rinku Singh!! Plenty of height on this, but not enough distance! Rajapaksa holes out off a slower ball! He advances down, looks to slog through midwicket but gets it right off the toe-end. Goes very high. And it's taken comfortably by Rinku at long-on.

Narine to Jitesh Sharma, , brilliant use of the feet! Narine gives it some flight at 88kph, and Jitesh skates down to get right to the pitch before unleashing a clean swing! He tonks it down the ground for a big six!

Umesh Yadav to Jitesh Sharma, , again Jitesh steps across the stumps. Wants to exploit the field with fine leg and square leg both in the ring. And Umesh plays into his hands this time as he dishes out a slower bouncer. It sits up nicely and Jitesh pulls it over short fine

Southee to Jitesh Sharma, , Good length just outside off, Jitesh clears the front leg, ensures he has a stable base and launches it with a clean swing down the ground. He clears the long-off boundary comfortably!

Southee to Jitesh Sharma,  Caught by Umesh Yadav!! Southee bounces back and dismisses Jitesh with the slower ball! It's an off-cutter floated up outside off, drifts away slightly in the air, Jitesh looks to slog over midwicket but it loops off a thick edge to short third. A dolly for Umesh.
Southee to Raza, , Raza is up and running straightaway! He's made this look easy! Back of a length on leg, not very short at all, but he pulls it superbly to the long leg boundary

Chakaravarthy to Dhawan,  Bowled!! Goes right through him! It's fired in at 106kph, hurries off a good length and Dhawan is beaten for pace on the back foot as he plays across the line. The ball crashes into middle and leg.
Thakur to Raza, , six over cover -  Slower one floated up outside off, right in the slot, and Raza hammers it all the way

Chakaravarthy to Sam Curran, , nowhere near the pitch after stepping out, but  Flat length ball that's pretty wide outside off, Curran dances down, reaches out and flat-bats it over long-on. An 87-meter hit!

Narine to Raza,  Caught by Nitish Rana!! Sliced in the air, and taken comfortably at extra cover! Raza loses his shape as he backs away from the stumps, looking to go inside-out! It's a length ball turning in on off, Raza miscues it off the outside half and Rana takes a good catch running back to his left from the circle.
Thakur to Shahrukh Khan, , misses the blockhole this time, and Shahrukh capitalises! He reaches out, drills it through extra cover, and it races away to the ropes
Southee to Shahrukh Khan, , slower one floated up wide of off, Shahrukh reaches out and muscles it through extra cover
Southee to Sam Curran, , now he goes at the stumps to Curran, instead of going wide, and gets whacked for six! Slower one floated up on middle, Curran clears the front leg and nails it over long-on
Sam Curran to Gurbaz, 1 run,  Good length on off, Gurbaz runs it down to short third man and sets off, Mandeep was struggling there, just missed too
Sam Curran to Gurbaz, , Gurbaz gets going with a massive hit. That's what he can do. Comes down the track and gets to the pitch of this one, lofts and the ball sails away over wide long-on
Sam Curran to Gurbaz, , half-volley on middle-stump, Gurbaz flicks and beats mid-wicket on the dive to his right, runs away and KKR are up and running with a good over first up

Arshdeep Singh to Mandeep,  Caught by Sam Curran!! Arshdeep Singh takes off on his aeroplane celebration. He strikes first ball. Short on the stumps, cramps Mandeep on the pull, miscued straight to the fielder at deep square leg. Bit of extra bounce foiled the timing of Mandeep and KKR lose their first wicket.
Arshdeep Singh to Anukul Roy, , half-volley on off, Anukul Roy stays back and lofts powerfully over mid-on, just bounces short of the cushions, so will be four

Arshdeep Singh to Anukul Roy,  Caught by Raza!! A big stare from Arshdeep Singh at Anukul Roy after getting the batter out. Dug in short outside off, Anukul fetched the pull but did not time it, finds mid-wicket who is on the edge of the ring. Arshdeep celebrates by staring down Anukul. Two in the over and he has given his side a dream start.
Sam Curran to Gurbaz, , half-volley on off, Gurbaz gets forward and lofts over mid-off, in the slot and he did not miss out
Arshdeep Singh to Gurbaz, , Gurbaz gets lucky, gives the charge and takes it on the full, slices the drive and it's in the air, but wide of short third man

Nathan Ellis to Gurbaz, no run, where was Venkatesh Iyer going? There was no run there. A slower ball on off, Gurbaz slogs and loses all shape, toe-ends to cover and Venkatesh dives to get back in, even as the throw from SRK misses

Nathan Ellis to Gurbaz,  Bowled!! Nathan Ellis cleans up Gurbaz. Pace-on and Gurbaz is nowhere near the line as he comes down the track to a back of a length delivery, cuts and misses, the ball clips off-stump. Poor shot and KKR are in big trouble now.
Nathan Ellis to Nitish Rana, , this is a shot Nitish Rana plays well. On a back of a length on the body, he plays the flamingo pull, beats deep backward square leg running and diving to his left
Raza to Venkatesh Iyer, , too leg-sidish. Full and sliding down, flicked between backward square leg and short fine-leg, runs away

Raza to Venkatesh Iyer, , a scream of anguish from Raza, good length on off, Venkatesh Iyer goes on the back foot and punches hard, beats cover-point on the dive to his left. Two boundaries to end the over
Nathan Ellis to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, slower ball dug in short on off, Venkatesh Iyer pulls to deep square leg

Raza to Nitish Rana, , Nitish Rana premeditates the reverse-sweep and takes it from outside off, gets it over short third man, who chases it but dives way too late, takes the ball along with him to the cushions
Rishi Dhawan to Nitish Rana, , Nitish Rana gets lucky, gives the charge and swings at a length delivery, the thick outside-edge flies away wide of third man

Rishi Dhawan to Nitish Rana, , Rishi Dhawan hasn't started well. Bowls it on a back of a length on the stumps, Nitish Rana gets forward and sets up before smashing the pull into the crowd at deep mid-wicket
Rishi Dhawan to Venkatesh Iyer, , hammered wide of long-on. Venkatesh Iyer picked the slower ball across him, pulls with all the power going behind the shot, placed it well too

Raza to Nitish Rana,  Caught by Rahul Chahar!! Straight to backward point. Was the quicker seam-up delivery on a back of a length outside off, Nitish Rana fails to keep it down and a sharp catch taken. Raza punches the air as he is thrilled. The timeout gets another wicket.

Rahul Chahar to Rinku Singh,  Caught by Raza!! Rinku falls and Rahul Chahar strikes first ball. Tossed up googly outside off, Rinku Singh goes for a slogsweep and toe-ends it, was aiming to clear the biggest part of the ground, finds deep mid-wicket where Raza makes no mistake. KKR stumbling again.

Harpreet Brar to Russell, , how hard has he hit that. Was a good length delivery on the stumps, muscled through Harpreet Brar's hands, harsh to call that a drop, was hit with extreme power and goes away straight down the ground
Rahul Chahar to Russell, , that's in the slot. Tossed up full on the stumps, Russell gets forward and smashes it over long-off, can't bowl there to this monster
Rahul Chahar to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, slower googly on the stumps, Venkatesh Iyer drags the slogsweep to deep square leg - no timing at all
Nathan Ellis to Russell, , mid-off is up, this is a fullish delivery on the stumps, Russell clears his front leg and muscles that wide of mid-off, in the air but no chance of catching that

Nathan Ellis to Russell, 2 runs,  Nathan Ellis digs this in short at off-pace on the stumps, Russell pulls and the top-edge loops to him, he is running back and drops it as it goes through his hands. Should have been taken

Nathan Ellis to Venkatesh Iyer, , , the free-hit is a half-volley on the stumps, seam-up and Venkatesh Iyer just holds his shape and lofts clean over long-on, did not try to hit it too hard, relied on timing as he leant back. And again Nathan Ellis has overstepped. Poor. Very poor
Sam Curran to Russell, , slammed over wide long-on. It's a low full-toss on the stumps, Russell clouts that over mid-wicket, such a clean strike

Sam Curran to Russell, , cheeky and effective. Russell was cramped by this short ball on the stumps, as he leant back, he just guides with an open face, using the bat like a ramp, over backward point and short third man

Sam Curran to Russell,  Caught by Raza!! Is that the game? The short ball dug in off-pace on the stumps, Russell does not get hold of the pull and holes out to deep mid-wicket. Raza takes it and Russell is aghast as he curses himself and walks off. Now the odds are against KKR. Sam Curran comes back well to get the massive wicket.
Sam Curran to Thakur, , what a shot! I0$. A short of length delivery on the stumps, seam-up and he has just casually whipped that from there over deep mid-wicket, pristine timing and it sails away

Arshdeep Singh to Venkatesh Iyer,  Caught by Rahul Chahar!! Arshdeep Singh strikes again. Digs it in short outside off, rises high and Venkatesh Iyer is on his toes trying to guide that, can only find backward point for a simple catch. Arshdeep Singh is blowing kisses into thin air as he celebrates.
Arshdeep Singh to Narine, , Narine can tonk them. A slower ball off-cutter on a length on off, angling into Narine who heaves it superbly over the deep mid-wicket fence, ends the over well
